# Second occurrence: -A again (flags == 0x10 at compare time).
# Kernel compare: first.flags (cleared to 0) vs later.flags (0x10) => NOT equal
#   (kernel/auditfilter.c:708  a->flags != b->flags returns 1).
# audit_find_rule does NOT find a match -> NO EEXIST -> rule loads fine.
# This is mere redundancy: au-W01 (Warning), NOT au-E03 (Error).
-A always,exit -S execve -k exec
